directions: Combine ingredients, adding eggs and margarine last.
Drop by spoonfuls on oiled griddle.
Cook on both sides until brown. Serve immediately.

title: corn chowder
directions: *Either a 20 ounce package of frozen or 1 can of whole kernel and 1 can of creamed corn.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Add alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt
butter in pan.
Brown meat and onion until transparent. Stir in remaining ingredients, except flour and milk. Cover
and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, 20 to 25
minutes. Combine flour and 1 cup milk.
Stir into soup mixture.
Boil
and add rest of milk; stirring often.
Do not boil.
Yields about 4 quarts.

title: cherry oatmeal
directions: Spread pie filling in a greased 9-inch square baking pan. In a bowl, combine next 6 ingredients. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over filling. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: karlie's easy oat bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Press dough onto bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: black magic chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix cream cheese and Hidden Ranch together.
Spread on crust.
Put chopped veggies on top.
It is delicious.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayo.
Fold in whipped cream (or Cool Whip), pineapple and cherries.
Pour into ice cube trays or a loaf pan and freeze.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add 2 cups milk.
Thick with 2 tablespoons flour mixed with 1/4 cup warm water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pyrex pie plate.
Sprinkle with hot sauce.	Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.	Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fancy baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and save the grease.
In bacon grease, cook the onions, bell pepper and wieners.
Then add other ingredients to this and cook on top of the stove for 15 to 20 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top to serve.

title: southern chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix chocolate with butter in saucepan. Place over low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Remove from heat. Blend in evaporated milk gradually. Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a bowl. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Blend in chocolate mixture gradually. Pour into pie shell. Combine coconut and pecans. Sprinkle over filling. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed and browned. Cover loosely with tin foil during last 15 minutes of baking, if topping browns too quickly. Cool for at least 4 hours. Filling will set while cooling. 10 to 12 servings.

title: garden salad
directions: Bring combined liquids to boil and cool.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn and pea salad
directions: Drain white corn, yellow corn and peas.
Add diced celery, onion, green pepper and pimento.
Bring salad oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and let set for 24 hours.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well the cake mix, pudding mix, 4 eggs, oil and 7-Up. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: dad's casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until color of meat changes. Add cottage cheese and set aside.
Cook noodles until half tender. Layer noodles and hamburger in casserole, starting and ending with noodles.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over casserole ingredients.
Beat egg and pour over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: rum cake(good, good)
directions: Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian soup
directions: In microwave, cook separately ground beef and vegetables. Combine cooked ingredients in kettle with remaining ingredients. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for flavors to mix well. Eat!

title: crunchy ham and swiss appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in corn flakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pork chop - potato dinner
directions: Arrange potatoes in baking dish or casserole.
Brown chops and arrange on top.
Combine soup, milk, salt, pepper and onions and pour over all.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: peas and cheese salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add peas, cheese, celery, pickles, onion and hard-boiled eggs.
Mix altogether and chill.

title: refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water; set aside at room temperature.
Mix and bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool cake 20 to 25 minutes. Poke deep holes through top of warm cake (still in pan) with a meat fork or toothpick.
Space holes 1 inch apart.
With a cup, pour gelatin mixture into holes.
Refrigerate cake while preparing topping.

title: cinnamon spread
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Serve immediately or refrigerate for later use.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add liquid. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Ice with Fudge Icing.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until clear.
Add a bit of salt to egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar for each egg.
After whites are stiff, add the cornstarch mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot torte
directions: Beat yolks until thick.
Add sugar and beat.
Add ground carrots and nuts.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand in oven until it cools down a bit.
(Bake in a spring-form pan.)

title: cinnamon nut coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square pan. Mix together egg, sugar, milk and butter.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix only until blended and pour into prepared pan.
In separate bowl, combine brown sugar, cinnamon, flour, butter and nuts and sprinkle over batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm, directly from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; save juice. Add melted margarine to stuffing mix.
Place approximately 2/3 to broccoli in bottom of a casserole dish.
Layer stuffing, mushroom soup, then onions.
Add remaining broccoli on top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour broccoli juice over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly using a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Serves 9.

title: refried beans
directions: Soak beans in water to cover in bowl overnight.
Drain.
Add boiling water to cover and salt pork.
Simmer for 2 hours or until tender.
Stir in chili powder, garlic and salt.

title: holiday cutouts
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Beat in egg. Add vanilla, sifted dry ingredients and cream; mix well.
Chill several hours.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness and cut with fancy cutters.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Decorate.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and green and red pepper in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Prepare lids and canning jars according to instructions.

title: warm crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, jalapeno liquid and jalapenos in medium-heavy pan over low heat.
Cook until cheese melts.
Stir in artichoke hearts and sour cream.
Stir often until mixture is hot. Stir in crab and Parmesan cheese.
Add salt and pepper and cook until mixture just simmers (do not boil).
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: italian stew
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in large pot.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook until almost tender (about 45 minutes to an hour). Add sausage and zucchini.
Cook until all vegetables are tender. Add macaroni and let simmer for about 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: quick 'n cheesy cocktail swirls
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine cream cheese, crumbled bacon, chopped onion and milk. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles. Press perforations to seal. Spread about 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese mixture on each rectangle. Starting at long side, roll up; seal. Cut each roll into 8 pieces. Place pieces, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheet. Lightly sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 32 appetizers.

title: chocolate jumbo cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in a large bowl. Add Wesson oil,
vinegar and water.
Mix real good.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch
baking
pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef chili beans
directions: Simmer chili beans and one can of tomato sauce in saucepan while ground beef is being prepared.
Brown ground beef, onions, green pepper and garlic in skillet until done, add one can tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Add to beans and simmer until blended.
Can be put in small containers and frozen.
It always taste better the following day.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to directions.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, leaving small amount for pan.
In bowl, mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and egg. Layer ingredients beginning with small amount of spaghetti sauce, noodles, beef mixture and cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: american chop suey
directions: Fry bacon; remove, leaving fat.
Cook onions until transparent; remove, leaving fat.
Fry hamburg.
Mix all together in large serving bowl.
Cook macaroni according to box directions. Add to bowl.
Heat soup just to boiling; add to bowl.
Mix all together and serve.
This is a winner.
Serves 8.

title: delicious crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble breads and add all remaining ingredients except margarine.
Pour mixture into crock-pot that has been sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Dot with margarine.
Cover, cook on high for 2 hours or 3 to 4 hours on low.
Makes 16 (6 ounce) servings.

title: hershey pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, Hershey bars and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt.
Cool, then fold in whipped cream.
Pour mixture into pie crust; sprinkle a few graham cracker crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown.
Mix soup, catsup and Worcestershire
sauce
together.
Pour
over chops.
Slice onion and spread over
chops
and sauce.
Let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Great served over rice.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery in butter until tender; remove from heat and add next eight ingredients.
Spoon into an ungreased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine melted butter and cornflakes; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: quick heavenly hash
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill 30 minutes or more before serving.
Double recipe, if need to.

title: japanese ingredients used in recipes
directions: Miso is a seasoning in paste form made from soybeans.
It has a salty and unique flavor and is used primarily in miso soup.
It is also used for marinating meats and fish before cooking and as a seasoning in boiled and sauteed dishes.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and nuts.
Press down in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: four layer coconut cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended. Add extracts, beating well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until blended after each addition. Stir in coconut. Pour batter into 4 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool on racks. Spread Coconut Filling between layers.

title: oven baked pot roast
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, place heavy duty foil (enough to wrap around roast and seal).
Rub roast on all sides with A.1. sauce. Set roast on foil in pan.
Mix together last 3 ingredients and pour over roast.
Seal foil tightly across top and at ends.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: tater tot casserole(chase pumphrey's favorite!)
directions: Brown Vegeburger and onion in oil.
Spread on bottom of round 2-quart dish.
Cook vegetables; drain and spread evenly over Vegeburger.
Top with undiluted soup.
Top with enough Tater Tots to cover.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed roll(polish dessert)
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter to 120°.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: finger jello or gigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin; dissolve completely.
Pour mixture slowly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill at least 3 hours.
To cut gigglers, dip bottom of pan in warm water for 15 seconds to loosen gelatin.
Cut shapes with cookie cutters all the way through gelatin.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In large pot, bring stock and water to boil; add zucchini. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
In skillet, cook onion in olive oil over moderately low heat, stirring until softened. Add curry powder; cook, stirring for 1 minute.
In blender or food processor, puree onion mixture with zucchini.
Return soup to pot. Add chickpeas, chicken and seasonings.
Simmer over moderately low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, until vegetables are desired tenderness. Adjust consistency by adding water, white wine or broth.
Serve hot, chilled or at room temperature, with croutons and dollops of nonfat yogurt or sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tsoi yan beng(sesame cakes)
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Gradually add the milk, butter and egg to the flour.
Mix into a smooth batter.
Spread thinly on a well-buttered pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into small squares when cold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery

title: peanut butter raisin chews
directions: Mix all ingredients except raisins.
Add raisins and mix well. Press out 1/2-inch thick in a pan.
Cut into pieces.
Chill before serving.
Makes about 25 pieces.

title: custard pie
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk; add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In a double boiler, melt cheese, margarine, milk and pepper until smooth.
Combine warm, peeled, cut up potatoes and sauce in a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Top with buttered croutons, parsley and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding.
Stir.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows to taste and nuts.
Chill.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Brown onion in drippings.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, ketchup, water, celery and seasoning.
Simmer sauce for 30 minutes.
Arrange franks in a shallow pan.
Pour barbecue sauce over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, flavoring, butter and pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and side comes out clean.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
well and bake in greased tube pan at 300° for
45 to 50 minutes.
While cake is warm, glaze with mixture of 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of 2 lemons.

title: crescent chicken rolls
directions: Cube and cook chicken; set aside.
Saute green onions in butter.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix everything together.
Open crescent rolls and leave in rectangle forms.
Total should be 8 rectangles.
Spoon chicken mixture inside.
Wrap up.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese.
Cook in oven as directed on roll package and serve!

title: grandma's french dressing
directions: Mix in blender or mixer for 2 minutes.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Cover diced potatoes and onion with water. Boil until tender. Add corned beef and bring back to boil. Mix flour and milk and add slowly. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Add chicken breast, then add soy sauce, garlic powder and mayonnaise.
Stir until well mixed. Serve over rice or noodles.
(May increase or decrease soy sauce, garlic powder and mayonnaise to taste.)

title: mandarin orange delight
directions: Mix pudding and Jell-O with water. Cook over low heat until thick. Cool. Add pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip. Mix and serve.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until well dissolved.
Add pecans and stir continuously until all syrup has well coated nuts and no syrup is left in pan.
Takes 5 to 8 minutes.
Spread nuts on buttered cookie sheet or wax paper. Let cool for 5 to 8 minutes.
Break apart.

title: fumi salad
directions: Dressing:
Mix sugar, pepper, oil, salt and vinegar together.

title: marie wisman's stuffed pickles
directions: Slice ends off of pickles.
With apple corer, core out insides of pickles, leaving approximately 1/2-inch hole.
Be careful not to split the sides.
Dry center of pickles out with strips of paper towels.
(If you have time, you can leave the towels in the pickles overnight in the fridge.)
Once the insides are dry, remove towels and stuff with cheese a little at a time so you don't split the sides.
Once the insides are full, place back into the fridge until the cheese sets, about an hour.
When you are ready to serve, just slice them.
One pickle equals about 6 to 8 slices.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
You will need 1 ungreased cookie sheet. On lightly floured surface, spread out crescent rolls and separate into 8 triangles.
In a small cup, mix mustard and Worcestershire together and using brush or teaspoon, spread sauce onto each triangle.
With scissors, cut each triangle into 3 smaller triangles, making 24.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Line baking dish with pineapple.
Cover with graham crackers. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over graham crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Add softened ice cream and mix well.
Fill pie shell and refrigerate until set.
Generously frost pie with Cool Whip.
Top with almonds or shaved sweet chocolate.

title: crunchies
directions: Melt morsels in top of double boiler.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: cora sue's peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, oleo and canned milk for 5 minutes (start counting when mixture comes to a boil).
Stir while boiling.
Turn down heat.
Take off stove and add Marshmallow Creme.
Stir well.
Add peanut butter.
(Use more or less per your taste.)
Stir well.
Put pan in cold water and stir until shapes.
Put into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.

title: spinach florentine stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Clean mushrooms; separate stems and caps. Chop mushroom stems. Cook spinach with chicken bouillon added to the water. When spinach is cooked, drain well. Saute chopped mushroom stems in butter. Combine spinach and seasonings with chopped mushroom stems. Lightly saute mushroom caps in butter or margarine until slightly browned; drain. Fill caps with spinach mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Place in a shallow pan and bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 18 appetizers.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients, except fruit, to make a smooth batter.
Pour batter over butter.
Do Not Stir.
Add fruit and juice.
Do Not Stir.
Cook in 300° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: walnut dream bars
directions: Blend butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and flour.
Press mixture firmly into shallow pan (two 8 x 8-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well; add remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture on top of previously baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Do not overbake.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: plum nelly cake
directions: Bake at 350° in Bundt pan (greased and floured) for 45 minutes or until done. Glaze with powdered sugar and milk.

title: sunshine ham and mac
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions to have 2 cups. Drain.
In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add Cheddar cheese; stir until melted.
Add mustard, ham, green pepper, hot sauce and macaroni. Heat to serving temperature or pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole to heat at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Yields 5 1/2 cups.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening; add milk and mix to a smooth dough.
Divide into six pieces.
Roll. Place apple on each piece; fill with cinnamon and sugar.
Wrap and fold.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oven steak dinner
directions: Place meat in center of aluminum foil that is large enough to make a good wrap over all the ingredients.
Sprinkle meat with soup mix and cover with vegetables.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Fold foil and seal to hold juices.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together and shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cook and freeze until solid. Put in bags in freezer.
Defrost before serving.
Makes 100 small balls.
(Can be enjoyed fresh from oven, too.)

title: fruit bread
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, banana, eggs, pineapple and cherries. Combine flour, salt and soda. Stir into mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir and pour into tube pan. Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes. Glaze with powdered sugar and cherry juice.

title: herb dressing
directions: Combine together, shake and chill.

title: tang dip
directions: Mix sour cream and Tang together.
Serve as a dip for fruits.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound out breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine milk, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken; set aside in the fridge for about an hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce in a bowl; cut cauliflower into pieces and place over lettuce.
Cut onion in thin ringlets and place over cauliflower.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over onion.
Spread a layer of mayonnaise over mixture.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper over mayonnaise; top with crumbled bacon and cover.
Make 24 hours ahead and toss salad before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cook raisins until soft, set aside.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sweetener and beat until smooth.
Add oil and beat 2 minutes.
Add applesauce and beat 2 more minutes.
Sift flour with baking soda and powder, cinnamon and nutmeg and add to mixture. Beat until stiff and add skim milk.
Stir until smooth.
Then stir in chocolate, zucchini and extract, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
For cupcakes, fill cups about 1/2 full. Bake 15 minutes.
For cookies, drop dough onto greased cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes.
Cool cake or cupcakes on rack for 10 minutes. Cool cookies about 5 minutes.

title: favorite barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over uncooked chicken in baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is done.

title: vegetable kugel
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrot in oil for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook spinach and drain.
Combine vegetables.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, melted margarine and matzo meal.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until firm.

title: buttermilk jello salad
directions: Combine
Jell-O,
pineapple and sugar.
Heat in a large saucepan
on
low heat until Jell-O is melted, stirring often. Put aside
and let cool.
Then add buttermilk and fold in Cool Whip good.
Put in a 10 x 12 x 2-inch deep pan and refrigerate until Jell-O
is
set.
If you like, add 1 cup of pecans after you put in Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs, then add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Cream together. Sift and measure out 3 cups flour, then sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix until thoroughly blended.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Place salad ingredients in a large bowl and toss.

title: that stuff gina made(brunch casserole)
directions: Cook sausage until completely done. Drain and remove sausage to a medium size bowl. In the same pan as you cooked the sausage put in the cream cheese and cook until melted. Pour over sausage and mix well. In a 8 x 11 baking dish roll out one can of crescent rolls and pinch together the perforations so that the dish is covered. Pour in sausage mixture and sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese. Roll out the second can of crescent rolls on top of the mixture. Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until the crescents are golden brown. Cut into 2 inch squares.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into
flour.
Add milk; stir until dough follows spoon around
bowl.
Knead	gently.
Place biscuits on greased cookie sheet.
Bake
at
450° for 10 minutes. Yields 8 to 12.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour pinto beans over ground beef.
Chop onion and green pepper and sprinkle over the beans, pour tomato juice over that, then sprinkle both cheeses over that.
Mix your cornbread according to package and pour over top.
Cook for about 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Delicious!!

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth, leaving 2 quarts of liquid to cook noodles in. Season vegetables with salt and pepper to taste. Cook large package of noodles in reserved broth until tender. Add chicken that has been boned. Combine mushroom soup and grated cheese. Mix chicken, vegetables and cheese mixture. Pour into a large casserole and heat in 400° oven until hot. Grated cheese may be added to top. Chopped mushrooms may also be added to this casserole and it may be served in pastry shells instead of a casserole.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Boil noodles and set aside.
Brown in skillet cabbage, chopped fine, browned in butter.
When brown, pour this mixture over the cooked noodles and serve hot.
Good as a side dish with pork.

title: mom's chili
directions: Saute in butter, onions, peppers and garlic.
Add ground chuck; cook and drain.
Place in large pot and add other ingredients.
(I add more chili powder to my liking.)

title: superb crab fondue
directions: Heat 2/3 cup Chablis, garlic, Velveeta cheese and Swiss cheese.
When melted, add liqueur.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce; add to cheese mixture.
Add arrowroot dissolved in a little of Chablis if the fondue is too thin.
Heat until the fondue thickens.
Add green onions and cook 5 minutes. Add crab meat and serve.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Toss together the first 8 ingredients.
Stir dressing ingredients together and pour over seafood salad.
Toss.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in at once strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour mixture in bowl and refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish or 12-inch shallow round baking dish.
Mix whole corn and creamed corn together with melted butter, sour cream and beaten eggs. Stir in corn meal mix.
Pour into prepared pan and let rest 10 minutes.
Bake for 30 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: main dish pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and make this mixture like a pie crust in a deep-dish pie pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and place this mixture in meat crust and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese over the top and bake 10 more minutes.
This is excellent to warm up for leftovers.

title: creamy primavera
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet.
Add broccoli, carrots and garlic; cook 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove vegetable mixture from skillet.
Melt remaining butter in skillet over medium heat.
Blend in flour, oregano and salt.
Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add vegetable mixture and remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: seafood fettucini(recipe for 14)
directions: Cook seafood in lemon juice and water.
Blanche veggies; boil in water.
Cook noodles.
Put cream in pan, first, on stove; heat it up.
Put 1 cup of grated cheese.
Stir until it melts; add spices and cook.
Add seafood.
Add fettucini and more cheese. Last, add veggies; toss.
Add more cheese.
Top it with parsley. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese and milk until light and creamy.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Use for raw vegetables.

title: hot kolbassi appetizer
directions: In skillet cook Kolbassi and beer covered for 10 minutes. Combine other ingredients and add to Kolbassi.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli cheese tarts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray miniature muffin pans with cooking spray.
Brush one side of each wonton skin with butter.
Carefully press wonton into muffin pan, butter-side up.
In medium bowl, combine egg and flour.
Beat with wire whisk until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into wonton skins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is set and wontons golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Crush graham crackers very fine. Then add all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Mix with hands.
Mixture will be very dry.
Spread and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: granny comer's fried apples(real good ... and easy)
directions: Cook with top on until tender.
Sort of a very chunky apple pie filling effect.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with 3/4 cup tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons dry mustard, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 2 tablespoons vinegar.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients for 7 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of mix into tube pan, greased and floured.

title: have fun sugar cookies
directions: Mix baking soda with milk, then add to ingredients.
Divide dough into 4 pieces.
Add a couple drops of different food color into each dough ball.
Top with sprinkles, candy pieces or dried fruit.
Mostly have fun with the kids.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil Dime Brand milk in can (unopened) for 3 hours.
Keep covered with water or can will explode.
Cool completely before opening can.
Pour caramel into graham cracker crust and top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Delicious!

title: grandma's summer sausage chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler and remove from heat.
Add egg and peanuts; stir.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on a sheet of wax paper or board.
Put chocolate mixture on the board and shape mixture into "sausage" links.
Sprinkle rolls with more 10x sugar. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate chocolate until hard.
Slice to serve and store in airtight container.

title: rice dressing
directions: Brown all meat in large Dutch oven.
Pour off grease.
Salt and pepper meat.
Add celery, onion and bell pepper and cook until vegetables soften.
Add chicken broth and cook about 45 minutes, until almost dried out but still moist.
Remove from heat.
Add cooked rice and mix well.
Add raw green onions and mix well. Serve hot.

title: grits-crispy parmesan squares
directions: In medium saucepan, bring salted water to boil.
Slowly stir in grits.
Cover; reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in 1 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spread this into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cool until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
In medium bowl, combine flour, seasoned salt, pepper and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Coat the grit squares on all sides until well coated.
Melt butter in skillet and fry grit squares until crispy on both sides.

title: yeast bread
directions: Soften yeast in cup of lukewarm water.
Stir and let stand 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, measure remaining liquid into large bowl. Add salt and sugar, then stir in softened yeast, shortening and flour.
Mix well.
Knead into a medium firm dough.
Brush with softened shortening, cover and let stand in warm place free from drafts until double in bulk.
Knead down and let rise again.
You can make yeast rolls, loaves of bread or cinnamon rolls from this dough.

title: stuffed cornbread
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Mix together with other ingredients and heat until cheese melts.
Make cornbread mix.
Pour 1/2 of cornbread mixture into skillet.
Pour meat sauce on top, then rest of cornbread mixture.
Bake cornbread as usual.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Place pecan halves in a pattern in bottom of unbaked pastry shell.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Gently pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and cook an additional 30 minutes.
(Filling should be slightly less set in center than around edges.)

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and cranberries.
Then add nuts and cranberries, mixing well.
Bake at 350° in a large loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: miniature pumpkin cakes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, pumpkin and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased and floured miniature Bundt pans or paper-lined muffin pans, filling three-fourths full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans immediately and allow to cool completely on wire racks.

title: deviled ham dip for chips
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix well with fork or blender.
Let set for couple hours.
Serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: creamy dutch pie
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients well with mixer.
Gradually add flour until mixture forms a soft dough.
Press into bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie pan.

title: old-time spice cake
directions: In medium bowl, beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Beat in soup.
On waxed paper, mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and cloves.
Add to soup mixture alternately with milk.
Begin and end with dry ingredients; combine well.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Divide batter evenly in the pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes (or do toothpick test).
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn on wire racks to cool completely.
Use cream cheese frosting.

title: bonnie's tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for few hours or overnight before serving to bring out flavor.

title: grilled bass with veracruz sauce
directions: Brush fish with 1 teaspoon cooking oil and sprinkle with lime juice, including cavity.

Place in well-oiled grill basket or on oiled aluminum foil with holes poked in it and place on the grill. Cook over moderately high heat until thickest part of fish is done. Meanwhile, make the sauce.
Heat olive oil in saucepan.
Saute onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Mix in tomatoes and olives and continue cooking over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and reserve; reheat when ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 4 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes, then drain.
Mix everything together.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: no fail microwave divinity
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 3/4 cup water in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 19 to 20 minutes or to 260° on candy thermometer, stirring every 5 minutes.
Pour hot syrup gradually over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed until candy thickens and loses its gloss.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: party sandwich spread
directions: In a bowl, mix together the eggs, Spam, carrots, onion, pepper, pickle and salt.
Add Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar. Mix well and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: butter twist cookies
directions: Cream butter and other shortening thoroughly.
Add sugar and continue to cream.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix well.
Use a 9 x 15-inch glass pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 425° oven.
If using metal pan, bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine
Crisco, brown sugar, water and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded measuring tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until cookies are soft.
Cookies will appear soft and moist.
Do not overbake. Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Place sheets of foil on countertop.
Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat cake mix, margarine and one egg together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar together.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ron's beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dip meat and brown in oil. Add all other ingredients and simmer for a couple of hours.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water. Cool. Mix Kool-Aid, juice, sugar and water. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: lemon poppy seed bread or cake
directions: Put ingredients in bowl as given.
Mix for 4 minutes.
Place in 3 small bread pans or 1 cake pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips and grated German chocolate.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° in greased tube pan.

title: green bean plaki(armenian bean-vegetable dish)
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to a boil.
Add green beans; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain and set aside.
In same saucepan, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender (5 to 7 minutes).
Stir in green beans, tomatoes, parsley, pepper and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot, cold or at room temperature. Garnish with additional parsley (and lemon slices if desired). Makes 3 cups (approximately 4 servings).
